    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 730</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">601.6411/3–1951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Legation in Hungary</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d265fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MRM1"
                            >McKisson</persName> (<gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_EE1">EE</gloss>), approved by <persName corresp="#p_RGF1"
                            >Reinhardt</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_HLR1">Higgs</persName>
                            (<gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_EE1">EE</gloss>),
                        cleared by Boykin (<gloss target="#t_CON1">CON</gloss>) and Muir (<gloss
                            target="#t_SSPR1">S/S–PR</gloss>), and signed for the Secretary by
                            <persName corresp="#p_HCK1">Huston</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 12, 1951—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>278. Fol pts, which are consistent gen US position re travel restrictions Hung
                    personnel US as previously notified Hung <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> ur note Mar 14 (ur 442 Mar 19 and Dept 241 Mar 12<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d265fn2">Telegram 442 from Budapest is not printed, but see footnote
                        4 to telegram 241, Document 727.</note>) are for ur guidance in event <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> raises question travel by Hung consular
                    officers US (ur 470 Apr 10<note n="3" xml:id="d265fn3">Not printed.</note>) and
                    may be used as you think advisable or necessary in circumstances.</p>
                <pb facs="0487" n="1453" xml:id="pg_1453"/>
                <p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Basic US position remains as stated ur note Hung <gloss
                                target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> Mar 14 (ur 442 Mar 19 and Dept
                            241 Mar 12): (a) removal restrictions on travel official Hung personnel
                            in US cannot be considered until Hung restrictions US personnel Budapest
                            are withdrawn and (b) meanwhile US restrictions will be administered
                            with due regard manner in which Hung restrictions are applied US
                            personnel Budapest. Same procedures which apply Hung leg Wash wld
                            therefore apply Hung consular offices NYC and <persName corresp="#p_CH1"
                                >Cleveland</persName> if reopened, and Hung consular personnel wld
                            be subj restrictions on travel.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>However, since NYC metropolitan area more extended than that Wash or
                                <persName corresp="#p_CH1">Cleveland</persName>, Dept prepared make
                            reasonable adjustment limits zone in which Hung consular personnel NYC
                            may travel without permit.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>If Hungs insist on explicit designation limits unrestricted zones, you
                            may indicate these as fols: Wash—18-mile radius from White House;
                                <persName corresp="#p_CH1">Cleveland</persName>—18-mile radius from
                            Public Square; NYC—25-mile radius from City <persName corresp="#p_HRL1"
                                >Hall</persName>.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
